<h2 id="controls">Controls</h2>

<div style="text-align: center; margin: 20px 0;">
  <button onclick="window.flipdotAnimation &amp;&amp; window.flipdotAnimation.start()" style="margin: 5px; padding: 10px 20px; background: #333; color: white; border: none; border-radius: 5px; cursor: pointer;">Start Animation</button>
  <button onclick="window.flipdotAnimation &amp;&amp; window.flipdotAnimation.reset()" style="margin: 5px; padding: 10px 20px; background: #333; color: white; border: none; border-radius: 5px; cursor: pointer;">Reset</button>
  <button onclick="window.flipdotAnimation &amp;&amp; window.flipdotAnimation.flipAll()" style="margin: 5px; padding: 10px 20px; background: #333; color: white; border: none; border-radius: 5px; cursor: pointer;">Flip All</button>
</div>

<h2 id="how-it-works">How it Works</h2>

<p>This flipdot animation simulates the classic electromechanical display technology where individual dots can be flipped between two states (black/white). The animation:</p>

<ol>
  <li><strong>Displays each character</strong> as a grid of dots on a black background</li>
  <li><strong>Animates from left to right</strong> with a realistic flip transition</li>
  <li><strong>Uses CSS transforms</strong> and transitions for smooth animation</li>
  <li><strong>Includes dot matrix overlay</strong> for authentic flipdot appearance</li>
  <li><strong>Supports responsive design</strong> for different screen sizes</li>
</ol>

<h2 id="customization">Customization</h2>

<p>You can customize the animation by modifying:</p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Text content</strong>: Change the message in the JavaScript initialization</li>
  <li><strong>Animation speed</strong>: Adjust the <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">delay</code> parameter (lower = faster)</li>
  <li><strong>Loop behavior</strong>: Enable/disable looping with <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">loop</code> parameter</li>
  <li><strong>Colors</strong>: Modify CSS variables for different color schemes</li>
  <li><strong>Size</strong>: Adjust font-size and character dimensions in CSS</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="usage">Usage</h2>

<div class="language-javascript highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="c1">// Create a new flipdot animation</span>
<span class="kd">const</span> <span class="nx">animation</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="k">new</span> <span class="nx">FlipDotAnimation</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="dl">'</span><span class="s1">container-id</span><span class="dl">'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="dl">'</span><span class="s1">Your Text Here</span><span class="dl">'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="p">{</span>
  <span class="na">delay</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="mi">150</span><span class="p">,</span>        <span class="c1">// Delay between character flips (ms)</span>
  <span class="na">autoStart</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="kc">true</span><span class="p">,</span>   <span class="c1">// Start automatically</span>
  <span class="na">loop</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="kc">false</span><span class="p">,</span>       <span class="c1">// Loop the animation</span>
  <span class="na">loopDelay</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="mi">3000</span>   <span class="c1">// Delay before restarting loop (ms)</span>
<span class="p">});</span>
</code></pre></div></div>

